## SECTION 5 — AUDIT TRAIL: IMPLEMENTATION RISKS

The following risks are documented for the strategy audit trail and must be reflected in the implementation roadmap (STEP 16 and beyond):

| Risk | Description | Mitigation |
|---|---|---|
| **Operational disruption from tool consolidation** | Terminating or consolidating active SaaS platforms (Workato, Peakon, Sage, Cognism, Outreach) without migration plans creates workflow gaps and data loss | Require a phased migration plan with a defined cutover date, data export/import verification, and parallel-run period before vendor closure |
| **Contract lock-in and early termination penalties** | Facilities vendors (Zagrebtower, Weking, TOG, Innovent, GPT, WeWork Singapore), insurance policies (Aetna, Jensten), and SaaS subscriptions may carry notice periods, break clauses, or ETPs | Align all Terminate and Consolidate actions to contract renewal windows; obtain legal review of ETPs before issuing termination notices |
| **Savings realisation delay due to migration costs** | Gross savings from consolidation and termination are partially offset by migration costs (data migration, re-implementation, retraining, agency transitions) | Build a net savings model for each P1–P2 consolidation group; flag migration costs in STEP 09 sizing; report net vs. gross savings separately |
| **Stakeholder resistance from business unit owners** | Department heads in Engineering (Cloudcrossing, Weking, Harmonic), Sales (Salesforce, LinkedIn, Cognism), Marketing (Big Frontier, HubSpot), and Facilities (TOG, Innovent, Zagrebtower) will resist vendor changes that affect their operating model | Secure executive sponsorship (CFO/COO sign-off) before any Terminate or Consolidate action above $20K; establish a vendor review committee with BU representation |

